    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prehistoric shaft-hole axes with symmetric cutting edges at each side of the shaft. Found in stone, copper and bronze. The double axe was a common religious symbol in Minoan Crete and was also used as a votive object.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
